{"body": "If it says KB it is clear what it means, kB would be base 10 and kb would be a different unit of measure altogether.\r\nI find it amusing that engineers will tell you the 2% error involved in mixing them up doesn't usually matter, while people building web apps think it does. :)\r\n\r\nAlso while Ubuntu and Mac OS may mysteriously count bits by si rather than binary powers, isn't Windows still the dominant consumer OS?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1058310", "created_at": "2011-04-26T14:01:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/292#issuecomment-1058310", "updated_at": "2011-04-26T14:01:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 292, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/nruth", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d2daf341883a14a6bf43bf25d655af81?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff1461909ac11780acf665caf329c10b9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d2daf341883a14a6bf43bf25d655af81", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "nruth", "type": "User", "id": 26158, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nruth/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386324bd3543c15101247b"}, "id": 1058310, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/292"}
